Hubris Holding Ltd., a unit of
 Sanlam (SLM)  Ltd., proposed purchasing additional stock of  Pan Africa
Insurance Holdings Ltd. (PAIL)  to take its share to a controlling stake
in the Kenya-based company offering life and general coverage.  Hubris Holdings currently owns 50 percent in Pan Africa,
the company said in a statement published in the Nairobi-based
Saturday Nation newspaper today. Sanlam is the largest insurer
based in South Africa by market value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  